  "text": "(g) Platelet-derived growth factor PDGF is produced by degranulating platelets present in the initial fibrin clot [CITATION_1] . The rate of production of PDGF decreases as the fibrin clot is degraded, and we model this production using a term with rate constant l 18 . This GF decays naturally at a rate characterized by the constant l 19 , and is further removed by fibroblasts through endocytosis [CITATION_2] at a rate characterized by the constant l 20 . Assuming this species diffuses at a rate characterized by D P , we thus have:",
